                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C.) In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi dei aeterni. <persName
                            ref="#people/9" key="#Emperor/king">Hlotharius</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/110">Hludouuicus</persName> divina
                        ordinante providentia <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatores</rs> augusti.
                        Dignum est, ut imperialis celsitudo, cum omnium fidelium suorum utilitatibus
                        consulit, maxime eorum convenienter et studiose praevideat et curam gerat
                        honoribus, qui sibi vinculo consanguinitatis adstricti artius fore
                        cernuntur. Igitur omnium fidelium sanctae dei ecclesiae ac nostrorum
                        praesentium futurorumque noverit sollertia, quia quondam amantissima <rs
                            key="#marriage">coniunx</rs> nostra praedicti Hludouuici augusti <rs
                            key="#parentOf">genetrix</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/10"
                            key="#Fiscal_reserve #Allocation_to_individuals #marriage #parentOf"
                            >Hirmingardis</persName>, dum adviveret, nostram petiit celsitudinem, ut
                        ei et <rs key="#childOf">filiae</rs> nostrae <persName
                            key="#Fiscal_reserve #Allocation_to_individuals #childOf"
                            ref="#people/11">Gisle</persName> in vita eorum <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve"
                            >confirmaremus</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/30"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                                ><rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>, quod est constructum in
                            honore dei et salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi</orgName> infra muros
                            <placeName ref="#places/9"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            >Brixiae</placeName>, sicuti et fecisse noscimur. Sed ea de hac luce
                        recedente placuit nobis denuo auctoritatis nostrae litteris idem <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">praeceptum</rs> renovare atque confirmare
                        in nomine memoratae filiae nostrae Gisle, sororis scilicet memorati
                        Hludouuici augusti, taliter, ut cum omnibus <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellis</rs> et <rs key="#Hospitals">senodochiis</rs> seu <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs> ad iam dictum monasterium aspicientibus,
                            <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            ref="#places/1913"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/1436">Alina</orgName></placeName> scilicet,
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve"
                            ref="#estates/1515"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve"
                                ref="#places/1914">Campora</placeName></geogName>, <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3516"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                                ref="#places/4339">Sextuno</placeName></orgName>,<orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/135"> monasterium in <placeName ref="#places/4"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                                >Luca</placeName>, quod <persName key="#Marquis/duke"
                                ref="#people/263">Allo</persName>
                            <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> edificavit</orgName>, et monasterium in
                            <placeName ref="#places/65"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            >Papia</placeName>, qui vocatur <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1421">Regine</orgName>, et<rs key="#Ports">
                            portum</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Ports #Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve"
                            ref="#places/43"><geogName key="#Ports #Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve" ref="#estates/2626"
                            >Placentinum</geogName></placeName> cum <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Hospitals"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1505">hospitale sancti Benedicti in <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Hospitals"
                                ref="#places/1915">monte Longo</placeName></orgName> nec non et
                        monasterium situm in <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1412"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Monasteries"
                                ref="#places/1828">Syrmione</placeName></orgName> vel cetera quaeque
                        ad praedictum monasterium pertinentia taliter, ut sepe dicta carissima filia
                        no[st]ra sororque sepe dicti augusti, dum advixerit, cuncta, quae supra
                        dicta sunt, <rs key="#Fiscal_reserve #Allocation_to_individuals">firmiter
                            obtinere usuque fructuario dominari possit</rs>. Unde et hos apices pari
                        consensu fieri censuimus, per quos firmiter sancimus et statuentes
                        decernimus, ut, quemadmodum praedictum est, universa, quae praescripta sunt,
                        ad praefatum monasterium pertinentia Gisla filia nostra, quandiu in hac
                        erumnali luce manserit, teneat, habeat atque possideat et ordine fructuario
                        gubernet atque disponat vel secundum regularem institutionem sancti
                        Benedicti, prout melius valuerit, iuxta dei voluntatem regat, postposita
                        longe cuiuslibet controversia vel inquietudine, eo dumtaxat tenore, ut, si
                        nos sepe dicte filiae nostrae superstites fuerimus, nostrae dominationi iam
                        fatum monasterium cum omnibus ad se pertinentibus reservetur. Unicuique vero
                        successorum nostrorum interdicimus et sub divina invocatione contestamur,
                        quatenus, si ipsa nobis supervixerit, nihil ex hiis, quae in hoc scripto
                        continentur, illi minuere vel auferre mol[i]a[tur]; quod si fecerit, optamus
                        atque omnimodis inprecamur, ut huius rei rationem deo universorum iudici
                        rectorumque rectori et domino dominorum plenissime reddat. Praecepta
                        interea, quae nostra sunt auctoritate firmata de stipendiis sororum inibi
                        deo militantium, volumus, ut fixa et stabilia permaneant per tempora
                        succedentia sine ulla immutatione. Et ut haec nostrae confirmationis
                        auctoritas pleniorem in dei nomine obtineat vigorem, manibus propriis subter
                        eam firmavimus et anuli nostri impressione [adsignari] iussimus. Signum
                        (MF.) Hlotharii serenissimi augusti. Signum (MF.) Hludouuici gloriosissimi
                        imperatoris. (C. NT.: <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Remigius"
                                >Remigius</name></persName> habebat signum; <persName key="#Notary"
                                ><name ref="Rodemundus">Rodmundus</name></persName>) Hrodmundus <rs
                            key="#Notary">notarius</rs> advicem <persName ref="#people/3908"
                            >Hilduini</persName> recognovi et (SR. NT.: Rodmundus notarius advicem
                        Hilduini recognovi. Remigius magister fieri iussit) (SI.) Data VI id. septb.
                        anno Christo propitio imperii domni Hlotharii pii imperatoris in Italia
                        XXXII et in Francia XII, indictione XV; actum <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential #Palatium #Villas"
                            ref="#places/4307">Gundulfi</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Villas">villa</rs>
                        <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential #Palatium"
                            >palatio regio</rs>; in dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
